# \f2\u-10179?\u-9000?\f1  \f0 How to Implement Static Virtual Accounts in Your App\par
\par
::< STEP-BY-STEP GUIDE >::\par
\par
---\par
\par
### \f2\u-10179?\u-8480?\f1  \f0 Step 1: Create a Virtual Account using Flutterwave API\par
\par
\f2\u-10179?\u-9143?\f1  \f0 When a **tenant signs up**, call Flutterwave API to generate their VA.\par
\par
**API Endpoint:**\par
\par
```\par
POST /v3/virtual-account-numbers\par
```\par
\par
**JSON Request Example:**\par
\par
```json\par
\{\par
  "email": "tenant1@example.com",\par
  "bvn": "22345678901",\par
  "is_permanent": true,\par
  "tx_ref": "TENANT12345_GREENVILLE",\par
  "firstname": "James",\par
  "lastname": "Okoro",\par
  "phonenumber": "08012345678"\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
**Response Example:**\par
\par
```json\par
\{\par
  "status": "success",\par
  "data": \{\par
    "order_ref": "URF_123456789",\par
    "account_number": "0123456790",\par
    "bank_name": "Wema Bank",\par
    "bank_code": "035",\par
    "expiry_date": null,\par
    "amount": null\par
  \}\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
\f2\u-10179?\u-9026?\f1  \f0 Save this data in your database in `VirtualAccounts` table.\par
\par
---\par
\par
### \f2\u-10180?\u-8233?\f1  \f0 Step 2: Design Database Tables to Store Virtual Account Info\par
\par
| Table            | Purpose                              |\par
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------ |\par
| users            | Users data                           |\par
| virtual_accounts | Stores VA number, bank name, user_id |\par
| wallets          | Wallet balance for each tenant       |\par
| transactions     | Credit/Debits to wallets from VA     |\par
| invoices         | Payment obligations (bills)          |\par
| settlements      | Vendor payments (estate \f4\u8592?\u8594?\f1  \f0 vendors)  |\par
\par
---\par
\par
### \f2\u-10179?\u-8940?\f1  \f0 Step 3: Set Up **Webhook** to Detect Payments\par
\par
When tenant funds their VA, Flutterwave sends webhook to your app.\par
\par
Webhook sample:\par
\par
```json\par
\{\par
  "event": "transfer.success",\par
  "data": \{\par
    "account_number": "0123456790",\par
    "amount": "25000",\par
    "reference": "GREENVILLE_LEVY_OCT",\par
    "sender_name": "James Okoro",\par
    "narration": "Service Charge October"\par
  \}\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
\f2\u-10179?\u-9055?\f1  \f0 Action your app will perform:\par
\par
| Action                                 | Description |\par
| -------------------------------------- | ----------- |\par
| Identify tenant using `account_number` |             |\par
| Credit their wallet                    |             |\par
| Mark invoice/bill as paid              |             |\par
| Update ledger/transactions tables      |             |\par
| Generate receipt automatically         |             |\par
\par
---\par
\par
